As we are using a forked repository, we need to be careful with modifying the original repository.

We should only change code when absolutely necessary and documenting the changes well.

We should only pull from the original repository when we are ready to incorporate changes into our fork.

We should only push to the original repository when we are ready to incorporate changes from our fork into the original repository.

We should always create a new branch from an updated main when we are ready to start working on a new feature.
